==Tangent vector on manifolds==
Let formula_35 be a differentiable manifold and let formula_36 be the algebra of real-valued differentiable functions on formula_35. Then the tangent vector to formula_35 at a point formula_1 in the manifold is given by the derivation formula_40 which shall be linear — i.e., for any formula_41 and formula_31 we have
