We further need the restriction that both formula_3 and formula_4 are non-negative, as we can see from the example formula_76 and formula_77 formula_78

The reverse inequality follows from the same argument as the standard Minkowski, but uses that Holder&#x27;s inequality is also reversed in this range.

Using the Reverse Minkowski, we may prove that power means with formula_79 such as the harmonic mean and the geometric mean are concave.

