<doc id="192044" wikidata="Q234571" url="?curid=192044" title="VCD (disambiguation)">
<text>Video CD or VCD is a video medium with a lower digital resolution than DVD.

VCD may also refer to:

* VCD Athletic, football team
* Voice command device
* Value change dump, a dumpfile format
* Vocal cord dysfunction
* Vibrational circular dichroism
* Vinyl cyclohexene dioxide, also known as 4-vinylcyclohexene diepoxide
* Victoria River Downs Airport, IATA airport code &quot;VCD&quot;
* Verkehrsclub Deutschland, a German mobility association</text><links>
